detail."},"339":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-20","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#workflows/:slug/graph`"},"340":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-21","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Visual graph tab."},"341":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-22","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#workflows/:slug/code`"},"342":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-23","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Source code tab."},"343":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-24","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#workflows/:slug/runs`"},"344":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-25","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"The workflow's runs."},"345":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-26","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#workflows/:slug/run`"},"346":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-27","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Start-a-run form."},"347":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-28","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#workflows/:slug/edit`"},"348":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-29","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Edit the workflow (admin)."},"349":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-30","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#approvals`, `#approvals/:id`"},"350":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-31","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Approval inbox / one card."},"351":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-32","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#schedules`, `#schedules/:id`"},"352":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-33","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Schedules / one schedule."},"353":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-34","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#agents/agents`, `#agents/skills`, `#agents/knowledge`"},"354":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-35","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"The shared catalogs (append `/:slug` for one entry)."},"355":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-36","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#runners`"},"356":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-37","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Runner health and pool."},"357":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-38","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"`#tokens`, `#secrets`, `#audit`, `#settings`, `#connect`"},"358":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-39","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Admin and setup views."},"359":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-40","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#route-grammar","content":"Segments are URL-encoded, so ids and slugs with special characters remain valid links. Some tabs accept aliases (for example `visual` for `graph`, `source` for `code`)."},"360":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-41","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#deep-links-in-api-payloads","content":"The API hands these links back so agents and integrations can point humans at the right screen without building URLs themselves:"},"361":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-42","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#deep-links-in-api-payloads","content":"Approval cards carry `deepLink` (the card) and `deepLinkRun` (the linked run), and their `context` includes workflow and run deep links."},"362":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-43","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#deep-links-in-api-payloads","content":"Run-creating responses (`run_workflow`, schedule run-now, draft submit) include link objects for following the run — its status, events, and artifacts endpoints."},"363":{"id":"/concepts/deep-links-44","page_id":"/concepts/deep-links","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/deep-links#deep-links-in-api-payloads","content":"When an agent hands off to a human — \"approve this\", \"read the logs\" — prefer relaying the payload's deep link over describing where to click."},"364":{"id":"/concepts/hooks","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","type":"page","content":"Hooks","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/hooks"},"365":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-0","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks","content":"Post-run hook profiles - admin-defined, bounded side effects selected per run that never fail a green run."},"366":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-1","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Profiles are bounded on purpose"},"367":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-2","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/hooks#selecting-hooks-per-run","content":"Selecting hooks per run"},"368":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-3","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"Hook outcomes never turn a green run red"},"369":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-4","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"370":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-5","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks","content":"A **post-run hook profile** is an admin-authored recipe for an optional side effect — publishing static output, pushing a work branch, calling a webhook — that runs *after* a run has produced its verified artifacts and its gates have passed. Hooks separate \"the work succeeded\" from \"the side effect happened\": callers opt in per run, and hook outcomes never rewrite a run's status."},"371":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-6","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Each profile has a fixed `kind` with a fixed set of config keys — anything else is rejected, so raw credentials or ad-hoc shell fragments can never be smuggled into a profile:"},"372":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-7","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Kind"},"373":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-8","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Effect"},"374":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-9","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"`static-publish`"},"375":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-10","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Copy verified artifacts to a configured target root (optionally with a public URL base)."},"376":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-11","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"`git-push`"},"377":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-12","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Push a work branch to a configured remote. Protected branches (`main`, `master`) are refused — merging to the default branch stays behind explicit run promotion."},"378":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-13","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"`webhook`"},"379":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-14","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"POST/PUT to an https URL, with optional headers and secret-backed headers."},"380":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-15","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"`vercel-preview`"},"381":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-16","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Trigger a preview deploy for a configured project."},"382":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-17","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"`custom-script`"},"383":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-18","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Run an allowlisted absolute command with declared, typed arguments — never a shell."},"384":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-19","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#profiles-are-bounded-on-purpose","content":"Profiles reference secrets by **name only** (`secretNames`), declare typed `params` callers may fill, and can restrict which workflows may use them (`allowedCapabilities`)."},"385":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-20","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#selecting-hooks-per-run","content":"Selection is explicit and two-sided:"},"386":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-21","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#selecting-hooks-per-run","content":"The workflow must opt in via `workflow.hooks.allowedProfiles` (a list of profile slugs, or `\"*\"`); no opt-in means no hooks, default-closed."},"387":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-22","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#selecting-hooks-per-run","content":"The caller selects profiles per run with `input.postRunHooks: [\"publish-docs\", …]`."},"388":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-23","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#selecting-hooks-per-run","content":"Preflight rejects a request naming a profile that is disabled or not allowed for that workflow, so ineligible hooks surface before a run is created."},"389":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-24","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#selecting-hooks-per-run","content":"Non-admin callers see enabled profiles in a caller-safe shape (slug, name, kind, params) — no paths, remotes, URLs, or secret names. Admins with `?all=1` see every profile with full config and readiness."},"390":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-25","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"Hooks run after the run's gates pass, and their results are reported separately from the run status:"},"391":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-26","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"Outcome"},"392":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-27","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"Meaning"},"393":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-28","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"`succeeded`"},"394":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-29","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"The side effect completed."},"395":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-30","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"`hook_failed`"},"396":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-31","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"The side effect itself failed."},"397":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-32","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"`hook_config_required`"},"398":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-33","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"The profile cannot execute — typically missing named secrets or a disabled secret store."},"399":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-34","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"`hook_blocked`"},"400":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-35","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"The profile was not eligible for this run."},"401":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-36","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"`skipped`"},"402":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-37","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"The hook did not run."},"403":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-38","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#hook-outcomes-never-turn-a-green-run-red","content":"A failed hook never rewrites a successful run into a failed one: the run keeps its own status and the hook results ride in the run output, aggregated into one headline hook status. `POST /api/hooks/{slug}/validate` is the admin dry-run: it reports `hook_config_required` with missing secret *names* only."},"404":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-39","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"405":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-40","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"406":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-41","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"407":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-42","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/hooks`"},"408":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-43","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`list_hooks`"},"409":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-44","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`?workflow=<slug>` narrows; admin `?all=1` includes disabled."},"410":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-45","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/hooks/{slug}`"},"411":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-46","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`get_hook`"},"412":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-47","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/hooks`, `PATCH /api/hooks/{slug}`"},"413":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-48","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`upsert_hook`"},"414":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-49","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"415":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-50","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/hooks/{slug}/validate`"},"416":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-51","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"`validate_hook`"},"417":{"id":"/concepts/hooks-52","page_id":"/concepts/hooks","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/hooks#api--mcp","content":"Admin readiness dry-run."},"418":{"id":"/concepts","page_id":"/concepts","type":"page","content":"Concepts","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts"},"419":{"id":"/concepts-0","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts","content":"A map of the core Runyard concepts and how they fit together."},"420":{"id":"/concepts-1","page_id":"/concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts#the-catalog","content":"The catalog"},"421":{"id":"/concepts-2","page_id":"/concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts#execution","content":"Execution"},"422":{"id":"/concepts-3","page_id":"/concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts#control","content":"Control"},"423":{"id":"/concepts-4","page_id":"/concepts","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts#platform","content":"Platform"},"424":{"id":"/concepts-5","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts","content":"Runyard is a self-hosted control plane for agent runs. You install **workflows** into a catalog, start **runs** of those workflows from the API, MCP, web app, or a **schedule**, and **runners** claim and execute them. The durable company asks those runs work on are **work items** — tickets on the Work board. Anything that needs a human decision surfaces as an **approval** card, sensitive values live in the encrypted **secrets** store, and optional side effects after a run are handled by admin-defined **hooks**. Access is governed by scoped **tokens**, and every page in the Hub is a shareable **deep link**."},"425":{"id":"/concepts-6","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#the-catalog","content":"**Workflows** — the unit of the catalog: a named, versioned definition with input/output schemas whose source lives as immutable bundles in the Hub database."},"426":{"id":"/concepts-7","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#the-catalog","content":"**Agents, skills & knowledge** — shared, reusable building blocks (agent roles, skills, knowledge resources) that workflows reference."},"427":{"id":"/concepts-8","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#execution","content":"**Runs** — a single execution of a workflow: lifecycle statuses, preflight and run drafts, events, logs, artifacts, reruns, and promotion."},"428":{"id":"/concepts-9","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#execution","content":"**Work items** — tickets on the Work board: the durable unit of company work that runs attach to, with a human-legible kanban lifecycle and a per-run execution flow view."},"429":{"id":"/concepts-10","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#execution","content":"**Runners** — the machines that claim queued runs and execute them via the Smithers engine, with tags, capacity, and optional sandboxing."},"430":{"id":"/concepts-11","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#execution","content":"**Schedules** — cron or one-shot triggers that create ordinary runs on a cadence."},"431":{"id":"/concepts-12","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#control","content":"**Approvals** — declared human decisions: approval cards with an explicit ask, per-kind consequences, and optional timers with fallbacks."},"432":{"id":"/concepts-13","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#control","content":"**Hooks** — admin-defined post-run side effects (publish, push, webhook) that run after a run's gates pass and never fail a green run."},"433":{"id":"/concepts-14","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#platform","content":"**Tokens & scopes** — bearer-token auth with the `api`, `mcp`, `runner`, `approvals`, and `admin` scopes; browser sessions carry exactly a token's scopes."},"434":{"id":"/concepts-15","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#platform","content":"**Secrets** — an encrypted store whose values are only ever decrypted into a run's child process environment, never returned by the API."},"435":{"id":"/concepts-16","page_id":"/concepts","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts#platform","content":"**Deep links** — the shareable URL grammar of the Hub web app, plus the deep links the API returns in its payloads."},"436":{"id":"/concepts/metering","page_id":"/concepts/metering","type":"page","content":"Usage metering & budgets","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/metering"},"437":{"id":"/concepts/metering-0","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering","content":"Per-run model-call usage as a first-class streamed signal, hard spend budgets, and the metering gateway at the inference boundary."},"438":{"id":"/concepts/metering-1","page_id":"/concepts/metering","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"Usage records and the run aggregate"},"439":{"id":"/concepts/metering-2","page_id":"/concepts/metering","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/metering#the-fleet-rollup-get-apiusagesummary","content":"The fleet rollup: `GET /api/usage/summary`"},"440":{"id":"/concepts/metering-3","page_id":"/concepts/metering","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"Budgets"},"441":{"id":"/concepts/metering-4","page_id":"/concepts/metering","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Capture paths: what is metered today"},"442":{"id":"/concepts/metering-5","page_id":"/concepts/metering","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/metering#selecting-gateway-metering","content":"Selecting gateway metering"},"443":{"id":"/concepts/metering-6","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering","content":"Every run durably records not just what it produced, but **what it consumed**. Each model call a run's child agents make is captured as a usage record, streamed as a run event while the run executes, aggregated onto the run, and included in terminal payloads — so dashboards, delegated callers, and budget enforcement all work off real numbers, never log scraping."},"444":{"id":"/concepts/metering-7","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"A usage record is one observed model call:"},"445":{"id":"/concepts/metering-8","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"Records fold into the run's persisted aggregate the moment they arrive:"},"446":{"id":"/concepts/metering-9","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"`costMicros` is micro-USD (1 000 000 = $1). When the provider reports the call's cost it is used verbatim (`costSource: \"provider\"`); otherwise the Hub estimates from a list-price table for well-known models (`costSource: \"price-table\"`) and records **no cost at all** for unknown models — totals are a floor, never a guess."},"447":{"id":"/concepts/metering-10","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"Where usage appears:"},"448":{"id":"/concepts/metering-11","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"`GET /api/runs` and `GET /api/runs/{id}` — the `usage` aggregate (and `budget` + computed `budgetStatus`) on every run object."},"449":{"id":"/concepts/metering-12","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"`GET /api/runs/{id}/usage` — the aggregate, the budget, per-call records, `budgetStatus`, and `budgetStop`."},"450":{"id":"/concepts/metering-13","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"`GET /api/usage/summary` — the windowed fleet rollup (below)."},"451":{"id":"/concepts/metering-14","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"`run.usage` events on the run's event stream and timeline, emitted in the same write that updates the aggregate."},"452":{"id":"/concepts/metering-15","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"Terminal response-endpoint payloads — `usage`, `budget`, and `budgetStop` fields, so delegated callers can bill or cap against real consumption."},"453":{"id":"/concepts/metering-16","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"MCP: `get_run_usage` and `get_usage_summary`, plus `get_run_status`/`list_runs` responses."},"454":{"id":"/concepts/metering-17","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"CLI: `runyard usage` (fleet rollup) and `runyard usage <runId>` (one run's detail)."},"455":{"id":"/concepts/metering-18","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#usage-records-and-the-run-aggregate","content":"The web app: a usage chip on run cards, spent-vs-limit budget pairing on run detail, and fleet-wide totals in `GET /api/dashboard` (`stats.usage`)."},"456":{"id":"/concepts/metering-19","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#the-fleet-rollup-get-apiusagesummary","content":"One call answers \"what is this deployment spending, and on what?\" for a time window (`?days=`, default 30, max 365):"},"457":{"id":"/concepts/metering-20","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#the-fleet-rollup-get-apiusagesummary","content":"`byWorkflow` is sorted by spend (highest first); `budgetStopped` counts runs that hit their budget inside the window. MCP: `get_usage_summary`; CLI: `runyard usage --days 7`. Totals follow the same floor semantics as everywhere else — unknown-model calls contribute tokens but no cost."},"458":{"id":"/concepts/metering-21","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"Run creation accepts an optional hard spend ceiling — as a top-level `budget` field or `input.budget`, on direct runs, negotiated runs, drafts, schedules, endpoint submissions, and reruns (reruns inherit the previous run's budget unless overridden):"},"459":{"id":"/concepts/metering-22","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"Budgets are hard stops, not advisories:"},"460":{"id":"/concepts/metering-23","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"**Before** each gateway-metered call, the Hub refuses to forward (`402`) if the aggregate has already reached the ceiling."},"461":{"id":"/concepts/metering-24","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"**After** every accepted usage record, the Hub re-evaluates; a breach emits `run.budget.exceeded&#x60; and terminates the run with the distinct terminal status &#x2A;*`budget_exceeded`** — never a generic `failed` — with the stop reason on `run.error` and `budgetStop`."},"462":{"id":"/concepts/metering-25","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"The runner observes the terminal status on its next poll and cancels the detached engine run, and the gateway refuses further calls from that run's token (`403`)."},"463":{"id":"/concepts/metering-26","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"An invalid budget is rejected with `400 budget_invalid` at creation (and surfaces as a preflight blocker in negotiation) — a requested cap is never silently dropped."},"464":{"id":"/concepts/metering-27","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"The CLI takes budgets as flags: `runyard run research --max-tokens 200000 --max-cost 2` (`--max-cost` is US dollars; the same flags work on `runyard preflight`)."},"465":{"id":"/concepts/metering-28","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"Every budgeted run also carries a computed &#x2A;*`budgetStatus`** — spent vs limit, per dimension — so no client re-derives the arithmetic:"},"466":{"id":"/concepts/metering-29","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#budgets","content":"`percentUsed` is the worst dimension (the one that will stop the run first) and `nearLimit` trips at 80%. The web run list shows a \"Budget 82% used\" chip on near-limit runs and \"Stopped at budget\" after a stop; the run detail page pairs spent / limit with the percentage. Runs that stopped on their budget appear in the needs-attention queue for 7 days so the recovery path (raise the budget, re-run) is visible, not archaeological."},"467":{"id":"/concepts/metering-30","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Usage is captured at the **inference boundary**, through two paths:"},"468":{"id":"/concepts/metering-31","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Path"},"469":{"id":"/concepts/metering-32","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Source label"},"470":{"id":"/concepts/metering-33","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Coverage"},"471":{"id":"/concepts/metering-34","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Key custody"},"472":{"id":"/concepts/metering-35","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Metering gateway"},"473":{"id":"/concepts/metering-36","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"`gateway`"},"474":{"id":"/concepts/metering-37","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Runs that select `metering: \"gateway\"` with the pi harness (`piModel`, `piBaseUrl`, `piApiKeyEnv`)"},"475":{"id":"/concepts/metering-38","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Provider key stays on the Hub; the child only holds a run-scoped gateway token"},"476":{"id":"/concepts/metering-39","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Runner-observed engine telemetry"},"477":{"id":"/concepts/metering-40","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"`runner`"},"478":{"id":"/concepts/metering-41","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Every claude / codex / pi CLI call the Smithers engine reports via its structured `TokenUsageReported` events"},"479":{"id":"/concepts/metering-42","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"Keys delivered per-run via the encrypted secretEnv channel (as before)"},"480":{"id":"/concepts/metering-43","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"**Gateway-metered runs** are pinned at claim time: the Hub mints a stateless per-run token, withholds the named provider key from the child environment entirely, and the runner materializes a per-run pi configuration whose *only* provider is the Hub's OpenAI-compatible gateway (`POST /api/gateway/openai/v1/chat/completions`; an Anthropic-shaped `/api/gateway/anthropic/v1/messages` is also served). The gateway authenticates the token, enforces the budget before forwarding, calls the run's configured upstream with the Hub-held key, streams the response back, and records usage from the provider's own response metadata (including streamed SSE usage frames)."},"481":{"id":"/concepts/metering-44","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"**Runner-observed runs** (the default, `metering: \"observed\"`) report the engine's per-call usage telemetry to `POST /api/runs/{id}/usage` with a stable per-call `requestId`, so replays after a runner restart never double-count. This is real, agent-reported usage from the engine's event stream — but the child still holds its own credentials (e.g. a Claude subscription token), so it is metered without being egress-locked."},"482":{"id":"/concepts/metering-45","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#capture-paths-what-is-metered-today","content":"**Not yet metered:** model calls that bypass both paths — e.g. a child agent calling a provider directly with an ad-hoc key from a tool script, or CLI paths the engine does not report usage for. Full egress locking (denying children any network path except the gateway) is a follow-up; the current sandbox shares the host network so the gateway pin is config-level, not network-level."},"483":{"id":"/concepts/metering-46","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#selecting-gateway-metering","content":"Gateway metering rides the same per-run harness selection surface as the pi custom-endpoint fields:"},"484":{"id":"/concepts/metering-47","page_id":"/concepts/metering","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/metering#selecting-gateway-metering","content":"Preflight blocks the run unless the selection is complete (pi harness, model, endpoint URL, and the Hub-secret name for the key) — a run never launches half-pinned. The endpoint key must be stored as a Hub secret; with gateway metering it is decrypted only inside the Hub per call and never enters the child environment."},"485":{"id":"/concepts/runners","page_id":"/concepts/runners","type":"page","content":"Runners","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runners"},"486":{"id":"/concepts/runners-0","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners","content":"The machines that claim and execute runs via the Smithers engine - registration, tags, capacity, health, and sandboxing."},"487":{"id":"/concepts/runners-1","page_id":"/concepts/runners","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runners#registration-heartbeat-claim","content":"Registration, heartbeat, claim"},"488":{"id":"/concepts/runners-2","page_id":"/concepts/runners","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runners#tags-and-execution-modes","content":"Tags and execution modes"},"489":{"id":"/concepts/runners-3","page_id":"/concepts/runners","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runners#capacity-and-pool","content":"Capacity and pool"},"490":{"id":"/concepts/runners-4","page_id":"/concepts/runners","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runners#sandboxing","content":"Sandboxing"},"491":{"id":"/concepts/runners-5","page_id":"/concepts/runners","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"492":{"id":"/concepts/runners-6","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners","content":"A **runner** is a machine that executes runs. Runners run the Runyard runner process, which claims queued runs from the Hub and executes each workflow via the **Smithers engine** (`smithers up <workflow> --input <json>`), spawning the local agent CLI as the worker. Nothing is faked: the agent runs on the runner's machine, and the Hub is the durable record — events stream back as run events, and outputs and traces are uploaded as artifacts."},"493":{"id":"/concepts/runners-7","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#registration-heartbeat-claim","content":"Runners speak a small machine protocol authenticated with **runner-scoped tokens** (see Tokens & scopes):"},"494":{"id":"/concepts/runners-8","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#registration-heartbeat-claim","content":"`POST /api/runners/register` — announce name, hostname, platform, version, tags, and capacity."},"495":{"id":"/concepts/runners-9","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#registration-heartbeat-claim","content":"`POST /api/runners/{id}/heartbeat` — periodic liveness; a stale heartbeat marks the runner offline."},"496":{"id":"/concepts/runners-10","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#registration-heartbeat-claim","content":"`GET /api/runners/{id}/next-run` — claim the next matching queued run. The claim payload carries everything the run needs, including decrypted secrets for that run only."},"497":{"id":"/concepts/runners-11","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#registration-heartbeat-claim","content":"Run lifecycle reports (`start`, events, `complete`, `fail`, artifact upload) are restricted to the runner that owns the run: the Hub checks the claiming token's identity, so one runner's token cannot touch another runner's runs."},"498":{"id":"/concepts/runners-12","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#tags-and-execution-modes","content":"Runners advertise **tags** (for example `local` on a workstation, `vps` on a shared remote pool). Two things match runs to runners:"},"499":{"id":"/concepts/runners-13","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#tags-and-execution-modes","content":"A workflow's `requiredRunnerTags` must all be present on the runner."},"500":{"id":"/concepts/runners-14","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#tags-and-execution-modes","content":"The caller's execution intent: `executionMode: \"local\" | \"remote\" | \"auto\"` (optionally a specific `runnerLocation`). `remote` targets the shared remote/VPS pool (default location `vps`); `auto` takes any matching runner."},"501":{"id":"/concepts/runners-15","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#tags-and-execution-modes","content":"Preflight checks this matching up front and reports `no_matching_runner` (blocker) or `runners_offline` (warning — the run would queue until one returns)."},"502":{"id":"/concepts/runners-16","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#capacity-and-pool","content":"Each runner declares a `capacity` (concurrent run slots) and reports its active runs; the Hub assigns work only to free slots. `GET /api/runners` returns every registered runner with heartbeat state, capacity, active slots, plus a pool summary — the same data the **Runners** page in the web app shows (`#runners`)."},"503":{"id":"/concepts/runners-17","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#sandboxing","content":"By default the runner executes workflows directly on its host. Setting `RUNNER_SANDBOX=bubblewrap` on the runner wraps each workflow *launch* in a generated Bubblewrap (`bwrap`) sandbox: the run's workspace is the only writable mount (bound at the same path inside and out), system directories are bound read-only, and the child gets a fresh workspace-local `HOME` — the host home directory, with its keys and credentials, is never mounted. Polling and control commands stay outside the sandbox. Installing `bwrap` is the deployer's responsibility; the runner verifies at startup that the sandbox actually works before claiming runs."},"504":{"id":"/concepts/runners-18","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"505":{"id":"/concepts/runners-19","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"506":{"id":"/concepts/runners-20","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"507":{"id":"/concepts/runners-21","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runners`"},"508":{"id":"/concepts/runners-22","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"`list_runners`"},"509":{"id":"/concepts/runners-23","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"Runners, heartbeat state, capacity, slots, pool summary."},"510":{"id":"/concepts/runners-24","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runners/register`"},"511":{"id":"/concepts/runners-25","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"—"},"512":{"id":"/concepts/runners-26","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"Runner protocol (runner scope)."},"513":{"id":"/concepts/runners-27","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runners/{id}/heartbeat`"},"514":{"id":"/concepts/runners-28","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"—"},"515":{"id":"/concepts/runners-29","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"Runner protocol."},"516":{"id":"/concepts/runners-30","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runners/{id}/next-run`"},"517":{"id":"/concepts/runners-31","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"—"},"518":{"id":"/concepts/runners-32","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"Runner protocol; claims the next run."},"519":{"id":"/concepts/runners-33","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runs/{id}/start` / `/complete` / `/fail` / `/events` / `/artifacts`"},"520":{"id":"/concepts/runners-34","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"—"},"521":{"id":"/concepts/runners-35","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"Runner protocol; run ownership enforced."},"522":{"id":"/concepts/runners-36","page_id":"/concepts/runners","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runners#api--mcp","content":"The runner protocol endpoints intentionally have no MCP tools — they are Hub↔runner machinery, not an operator surface."},"523":{"id":"/concepts/runs","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"page","content":"Runs","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs"},"524":{"id":"/concepts/runs-0","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs","content":"The run lifecycle, preflight and run drafts, events and artifacts, reruns, and promotion."},"525":{"id":"/concepts/runs-1","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Lifecycle"},"526":{"id":"/concepts/runs-2","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"Paused runs (recoverable interruptions)"},"527":{"id":"/concepts/runs-3","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#failure-classes","content":"Failure classes"},"528":{"id":"/concepts/runs-4","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#usage-and-budgets","content":"Usage and budgets"},"529":{"id":"/concepts/runs-5","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#the-needs-attention-queue","content":"The needs-attention queue"},"530":{"id":"/concepts/runs-6","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#preflight-and-run-drafts-negotiation","content":"Preflight and run drafts (negotiation)"},"531":{"id":"/concepts/runs-7","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#events-timeline-logs-artifacts","content":"Events, timeline, logs, artifacts"},"532":{"id":"/concepts/runs-8","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#reruns-and-promotion","content":"Reruns and promotion"},"533":{"id":"/concepts/runs-9","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#response-endpoints","content":"Response endpoints"},"534":{"id":"/concepts/runs-10","page_id":"/concepts/runs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"535":{"id":"/concepts/runs-11","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs","content":"A **run** is a single execution of a workflow with a JSON input. Runs are created from the API, MCP, web app, CLI, a schedule, or a workflow endpoint; a runner claims each queued run and executes it, streaming events, logs, and artifacts back to the Hub as the durable record."},"536":{"id":"/concepts/runs-12","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Status"},"537":{"id":"/concepts/runs-13","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Meaning"},"538":{"id":"/concepts/runs-14","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`waiting_approval`"},"539":{"id":"/concepts/runs-15","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Held for a human decision before entering the queue (see Approvals). Never times out — waiting cannot fail a run."},"540":{"id":"/concepts/runs-16","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`queued`"},"541":{"id":"/concepts/runs-17","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Ready for a matching runner to claim."},"542":{"id":"/concepts/runs-18","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`assigned`"},"543":{"id":"/concepts/runs-19","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Claimed by a runner, not yet started."},"544":{"id":"/concepts/runs-20","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`running`"},"545":{"id":"/concepts/runs-21","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Executing on the runner."},"546":{"id":"/concepts/runs-22","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`paused`"},"547":{"id":"/concepts/runs-23","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Parked on a recoverable external interruption (provider credits or quota exhausted, or an operator pause). Non-terminal: the run keeps its engine checkpoint, frees its runner slot, is never reaped, and waits for resume or cancel."},"548":{"id":"/concepts/runs-24","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`succeeded`"},"549":{"id":"/concepts/runs-25","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Finished with outputs."},"550":{"id":"/concepts/runs-26","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`cancelled`"},"551":{"id":"/concepts/runs-27","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Stopped by an operator or a rejected approval — a human \"no\" is a decision, not a failure."},"552":{"id":"/concepts/runs-28","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"`failed` (+ classes)"},"553":{"id":"/concepts/runs-29","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Terminal failure; see failure classes below."},"554":{"id":"/concepts/runs-30","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#lifecycle","content":"Terminal states are final: late reports racing a terminal state are absorbed idempotently rather than overwriting the first decision."},"555":{"id":"/concepts/runs-31","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"When execution is interrupted by a condition a human can fix — the classic case is **the provider account ran out of credits** — the run parks as `paused` instead of failing. Pause metadata lives on `run.pause`:"},"556":{"id":"/concepts/runs-32","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"**How runs pause.** The metering gateway pauses a gateway-metered run when the upstream provider answers with a credit/quota-exhaustion response (e.g. HTTP 402) — a structured signal at the inference boundary. The runner pauses a run whose engine failure text clearly means exhausted credits/quota (today Smithers 0.22 exposes no structured pause/credit event, so this path classifies the engine's error text; it will sharpen as engines emit richer signals). Operators can pause explicitly via `POST /api/runs/{id}/pause` (`pause_run`, `runyard pause`)."},"557":{"id":"/concepts/runs-33","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"**What paused means.** The run releases its runner slot (a parked run never occupies capacity), keeps its `runner_id` so resume lands on the runner holding the local engine checkpoint, and is exempt from liveness/stall/deadline reaping. `run.paused` / `run.resumed` timeline events record the transitions."},"558":{"id":"/concepts/runs-34","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"**Resume.** `POST /api/runs/{id}/resume` (`resume_run`, `runyard resume`) re-queues the *same* run. With a recorded checkpoint it continues via the engine's resume (`smithers up --resume`); without one it re-runs from scratch and the response (`resume.strategy: \"rerun_from_scratch\"`) plus the run timeline say so explicitly. Cancel still works from `paused`."},"559":{"id":"/concepts/runs-35","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"**Resume strategies.** The resume body optionally forces a strategy: `{\"strategy\": \"rerun_from_scratch\"}` discards the recorded checkpoint *and* clears the runner pin so any live runner can take the run (`runyard resume --from-scratch`, the web \"Restart from scratch\" button); `{\"strategy\": \"smithers_resume\"}` insists on the checkpoint and answers `409` when none is recorded. Omitted, the strategy resolves automatically."},"560":{"id":"/concepts/runs-36","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"**Offline checkpoint runner.** A checkpointed resume only executes once the runner holding the checkpoint claims it. If that runner is offline, the resume still succeeds but the response carries a `warning` (and the `run.resumed` event records it): the run stays queued until the runner reconnects, or you resume again with `rerun_from_scratch` to run anywhere."},"561":{"id":"/concepts/runs-37","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"**Resume failure.** If the runner cannot find the recorded checkpoint in its local `.smithers` state (state cleaned, workspace replaced), it does **not** hang or fake a timeout: it emits `runner.resume_checkpoint_missing` and re-parks the run as `paused` with `reason: \"resume_failed\"` and the stale checkpoint dropped, so the next resume honestly re-runs from scratch. (The engine validates `--resume` inside its detached child, so the Hub runner verifies the checkpoint with `smithers inspect` *before* launching.)"},"562":{"id":"/concepts/runs-38","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#paused-runs-recoverable-interruptions","content":"**Not a budget stop.** `budget_exceeded` remains a distinct *terminal* status for the Hub's own hard spend ceiling; a budget breach is never converted into a pause."},"563":{"id":"/concepts/runs-39","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#failure-classes","content":"Failures are classified into specific terminal statuses so operators can tell config problems from real failures: `failed` (generic), `blocked_by_gate` (a verification gate failed), `blocked_by_preflight` (the run could never start as configured), `provider_limited` (rate limits/quota), `timed_out`, `invalid_output` (schema mismatch), `infra_unavailable` (network/runner infrastructure), `needs_human`, and `budget_exceeded` (the run's metered usage reached its spend budget and it was hard-stopped)."},"564":{"id":"/concepts/runs-40","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#usage-and-budgets","content":"Runs also meter the model calls they consume: per-call usage records stream as `run.usage` events and aggregate onto the run as `usage` (`totalTokens`, `costMicros`, `byModel`, ...), and run creation accepts an optional `budget: { maxTokens?, maxCostMicros? }` hard ceiling. Budgeted runs additionally carry a computed `budgetStatus` (spent vs limit, remaining, percent used, `nearLimit` at 80%) in list and detail payloads. See Usage metering & budgets for the data model, the fleet rollup (`GET /api/usage/summary`), the metering gateway, and budget enforcement."},"565":{"id":"/concepts/runs-41","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#the-needs-attention-queue","content":"`GET /api/runs/attention` (`list_attention_runs`, `runyard attention`) returns every run whose next step is a human action, grouped with counts:"},"566":{"id":"/concepts/runs-42","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#the-needs-attention-queue","content":"**`paused`** — resume them once the interruption is fixed;"},"567":{"id":"/concepts/runs-43","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#the-needs-attention-queue","content":"**`waitingApproval`** — a decision is pending on an approval card;"},"568":{"id":"/concepts/runs-44","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#the-needs-attention-queue","content":"**`budgetStopped`** — hit their spend ceiling in the last 7 days; raise the budget and re-run to finish the work."},"569":{"id":"/concepts/runs-45","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#the-needs-attention-queue","content":"`counts` also includes `pendingApprovals` (open approval cards). The web Home view renders this as a triage strip above the runs list with resume/review/inspect actions inline; it disappears entirely when nothing needs a human. `GET /api/runs?status=paused` (or any other status) remains the raw filter underneath."},"570":{"id":"/concepts/runs-46","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#preflight-and-run-drafts-negotiation","content":"Before anything is enqueued, Runyard can run a **deterministic preflight**: schema checks on required input fields, runner/tag availability, secret presence, hook eligibility, and workflow source resolution. The result is `ready`, `needs_input` (with `questions[]` the caller can answer), or `blocked` (with `blockers[]` only an operator can fix), plus warnings, suggested defaults, and a `nextAction` hint."},"571":{"id":"/concepts/runs-47","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#preflight-and-run-drafts-negotiation","content":"Three ways to use it:"},"572":{"id":"/concepts/runs-48","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#preflight-and-run-drafts-negotiation","content":"`POST /api/workflows/{id}/preflight` — stateless report, nothing created."},"573":{"id":"/concepts/runs-49","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#preflight-and-run-drafts-negotiation","content":"`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run` with `negotiate: true` — enqueue only when ready; otherwise the negotiation state and a saved draft come back instead of a doomed run."},"574":{"id":"/concepts/runs-50","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#preflight-and-run-drafts-negotiation","content":"**Run drafts** — a draft is a proposed run that has *not* been enqueued. Create it, patch its input to answer questions (each patch re-preflights), then submit; submit re-preflights and returns 202 with the run only when ready (422 `needs_input` / 409 `blocked` otherwise)."},"575":{"id":"/concepts/runs-51","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#preflight-and-run-drafts-negotiation","content":"`input.title` is recommended for agent-created runs: a short human-readable title used in run lists, approval cards, and handoff."},"576":{"id":"/concepts/runs-52","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#events-timeline-logs-artifacts","content":"Runners append structured **events** as the run progresses; `GET /api/runs/{id}/events/stream` serves them live over SSE and `GET /api/runs/{id}/timeline` merges status transitions, events, and artifacts into one ascending feed (with `since`/`limit` paging). Log lines are at `/logs`, a condensed log summary and diagnostics at `/diagnostics`, and uploaded **artifacts** (outputs, traces, files) at `/artifacts`, downloadable by artifact id."},"577":{"id":"/concepts/runs-53","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#reruns-and-promotion","content":"**Rerun** — `POST /api/runs/{id}/rerun` creates a linked new run with the same input, optionally edited."},"578":{"id":"/concepts/runs-54","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#reruns-and-promotion","content":"**Promotion** — for runs that mutated an isolated git worktree, `POST /api/runs/{id}/promote` merges the successful run's work into its target branch, runs gates, pushes, and cleans up the branch/worktree. Merging to the default branch always goes through promotion, never through a hook."},"579":{"id":"/concepts/runs-55","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#response-endpoints","content":"A run request may include `responseEndpoint: {type: \"http\" | \"telegram\", config}` so the terminal-state reply is delivered to the caller when the run finishes. Delivery state is reported in `responseEndpoints[]` on `GET /api/runs/{id}`; polling that endpoint remains the canonical fallback."},"580":{"id":"/concepts/runs-56","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"581":{"id":"/concepts/runs-57","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"582":{"id":"/concepts/runs-58","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run`"},"583":{"id":"/concepts/runs-59","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`run_workflow`"},"584":{"id":"/concepts/runs-60","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/workflows/{id}/preflight`"},"585":{"id":"/concepts/runs-61","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`preflight_workflow`"},"586":{"id":"/concepts/runs-62","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`GET/POST /api/run-drafts`, `GET/PATCH /api/run-drafts/{id}`, `POST .../submit`, `POST .../discard`"},"587":{"id":"/concepts/runs-63","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`list_run_drafts`, `create_run_draft`, `get_run_draft`, `update_run_draft`, `submit_run_draft`, `discard_run_draft`"},"588":{"id":"/concepts/runs-64","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runs`, `GET /api/runs/{id}`"},"589":{"id":"/concepts/runs-65","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`list_runs`, `get_run_status`"},"590":{"id":"/concepts/runs-66","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runs/attention`"},"591":{"id":"/concepts/runs-67","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`list_attention_runs`"},"592":{"id":"/concepts/runs-68","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runs/{id}/usage`, `GET /api/usage/summary`"},"593":{"id":"/concepts/runs-69","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`get_run_usage`, `get_usage_summary`"},"594":{"id":"/concepts/runs-70","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runs/{id}/events`, `/timeline`, `/diagnostics`, `/logs`"},"595":{"id":"/concepts/runs-71","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`get_run_events`, `get_run_timeline`, `get_run_diagnostics`, `get_run_logs`"},"596":{"id":"/concepts/runs-72","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runs/{id}/artifacts`, `GET /api/artifacts`, `GET /api/artifacts/{id}/download`"},"597":{"id":"/concepts/runs-73","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`get_run_artifacts`, `search_artifacts`, `download_artifact`"},"598":{"id":"/concepts/runs-74","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runs/{id}/cancel`"},"599":{"id":"/concepts/runs-75","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`cancel_run`"},"600":{"id":"/concepts/runs-76","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runs/{id}/pause`"},"601":{"id":"/concepts/runs-77","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`pause_run`"},"602":{"id":"/concepts/runs-78","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runs/{id}/resume`"},"603":{"id":"/concepts/runs-79","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`resume_run`"},"604":{"id":"/concepts/runs-80","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runs/{id}/rerun`"},"605":{"id":"/concepts/runs-81","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`rerun_workflow_run`"},"606":{"id":"/concepts/runs-82","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/runs/{id}/promote`"},"607":{"id":"/concepts/runs-83","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`promote_run`"},"608":{"id":"/concepts/runs-84","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/dashboard`"},"609":{"id":"/concepts/runs-85","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"`get_dashboard`"},"610":{"id":"/concepts/runs-86","page_id":"/concepts/runs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/runs#api--mcp","content":"The `start`/`complete`/`fail`/event-append and artifact-upload endpoints under `/api/runs/{id}` are the runner protocol (runner-scoped tokens, run ownership enforced) — see Runners."},"611":{"id":"/concepts/schedules","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"page","content":"Schedules","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules"},"612":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-0","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules","content":"Cron and one-shot triggers that create ordinary workflow runs on a cadence."},"613":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-1","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules#cron-expressions-and-timezones","content":"Cron expressions and timezones"},"614":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-2","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules#one-shot-schedules","content":"One-shot schedules"},"615":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-3","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules#schedules-from-board-definitions","content":"Schedules from board definitions"},"616":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-4","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules#enable-disable-run-now","content":"Enable, disable, run now"},"617":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-5","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules#what-a-fire-produces","content":"What a fire produces"},"618":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-6","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules#repair-and-reconciliation","content":"Repair and Reconciliation"},"619":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-7","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"620":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-8","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules","content":"A **schedule** runs a workflow automatically: either recurring on a **cron** cadence or once at a fixed **runAt** timestamp. Each fire creates a completely ordinary run with the schedule's stored input — it appears in run lists, honors the workflow's approval policy, and is executed by whatever runner matches."},"621":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-9","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#cron-expressions-and-timezones","content":"Runyard uses standard **5-field cron** (`minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week`) with ranges (`a-b`), lists (`a,b,c`), steps (`*/n`, `a-b/n`), month/weekday names (`jan..dec`, `sun..sat`), and the aliases `@yearly`, `@monthly`, `@weekly`, `@daily`, `@hourly`. There is no seconds field — the Hub ticks at minute granularity."},"622":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-10","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#cron-expressions-and-timezones","content":"Every schedule has an **IANA timezone** (default `UTC`); the expression is evaluated against wall-clock time in that zone, so DST shifts are honored."},"623":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-11","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#cron-expressions-and-timezones","content":"The preview returns a human-readable description plus the next fire instants — nothing is created."},"624":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-12","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#one-shot-schedules","content":"Provide `runAt` (an ISO timestamp) instead of `cron` to fire exactly once. A schedule takes one or the other."},"625":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-13","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#schedules-from-board-definitions","content":"A portable board definition can carry a `schedules[]` array. Importing the definition creates each listed schedule keyed by `board:<slug>:<schedule-slug>` so re-imports reconcile in-place instead of duplicating cron jobs. The optional `laneId` on a definition schedule marks which lane's trigger the schedule backs — the factory template uses it for the \"Ready → In motion\" nightly smoke check. This is the write path a board's lane trigger uses to hook into the existing schedule surface without a second round-trip."},"626":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-14","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#schedules-from-board-definitions","content":"The RunYard Development Factory example also ships a disabled daily `product-workflow` schedule for roadmap shaping: `0 9 * * *` in `America/New_York`, `execute: true`, and `laneId: \"triaged\"`. When an operator enables it, the child implementation runs execute sequentially in isolated review branches; `main` is changed only by explicit promotion."},"627":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-15","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#enable-disable-run-now","content":"**Disable** stops a schedule from firing without deleting it; **enable** resumes the cadence. Both are admin actions."},"628":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-16","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#enable-disable-run-now","content":"**Run now** fires the schedule immediately without changing its cadence — useful for testing input before the next scheduled fire."},"629":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-17","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#enable-disable-run-now","content":"Each schedule tracks `nextRunAt`, `lastRunAt`, the last run id, and the last run's current terminal status, all visible on the Schedules page (`#schedules`) and in the API. Enabled schedules must target an enabled workflow. If a workflow is disabled later, RunYard fails safe: dependent enabled schedules are atomically auto-disabled, keep their history, and expose `state: \"broken\"`, `brokenReason`, `disabledReason`, and `operatorAction` in API/MCP/Web payloads. Re-enable only after editing the schedule to an enabled workflow."},"630":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-18","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#what-a-fire-produces","content":"Every fire dispatches a normal run whose origin identifies the schedule:"},"631":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-19","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#what-a-fire-produces","content":"(`trigger` is `ticker` for cadence fires, `manual` for run-now.) The run also gets a `run.scheduled` event recording the schedule, cron, and timezone. If the workflow's approval policy requires it, the run starts in `waiting_approval` like any other run. External automation that wants first-class Scheduled provenance should call `run_schedule_now`; calling `run_workflow` directly remains a token/API/MCP-origin run."},"632":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-20","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#repair-and-reconciliation","content":"Startup runs an idempotent reconciliation pass after migrations and catalog seeding. It auto-disables any legacy enabled schedule whose workflow is missing or disabled, writes `lastStatus: \"broken_reference\"`, records an audit entry, and leaves schedule/run history intact. This is the live-data repair path for stale schedules such as old nightly jobs pointing at disabled workflows; no retargeting or deletion is performed."},"633":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-21","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"634":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-22","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"635":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-23","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"636":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-24","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/schedules`"},"637":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-25","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`list_schedules`"},"638":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-26","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Includes next/last run and a readable preview."},"639":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-27","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/schedules/preview`"},"640":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-28","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`preview_schedule`"},"641":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-29","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Query: `cron`, `timezone`."},"642":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-30","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/schedules/{id}`"},"643":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-31","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`get_schedule`"},"644":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-32","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/schedules`"},"645":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-33","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`create_schedule`"},"646":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-34","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Admin. Body: `name`, `workflowSlug`, `cron` or `runAt`, `timezone`, `input`, `enabled`."},"647":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-35","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`PATCH /api/schedules/{id}`"},"648":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-36","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`update_schedule`"},"649":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-37","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"650":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-38","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/schedules/{id}/enable`"},"651":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-39","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`enable_schedule`"},"652":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-40","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"653":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-41","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/schedules/{id}/disable`"},"654":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-42","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`disable_schedule`"},"655":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-43","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"656":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-44","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/schedules/{id}/run-now`"},"657":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-45","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`run_schedule_now`"},"658":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-46","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Fires immediately; rate-limited."},"659":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-47","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`DELETE /api/schedules/{id}`"},"660":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-48","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"`delete_schedule`"},"661":{"id":"/concepts/schedules-49","page_id":"/concepts/schedules","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/schedules#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"662":{"id":"/concepts/secrets","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","type":"page","content":"Secrets","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/secrets"},"663":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-0","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets","content":"The encrypted secret store - admin-managed, listable by name only, delivered to runs at claim time and never returned by the API."},"664":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-1","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/secrets#management-admin-only","content":"Management (admin only)"},"665":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-2","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"How runs get secrets"},"666":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-3","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"667":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-4","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets","content":"Runyard keeps reusable credentials (API keys, deploy tokens) in an **encrypted secret store** on the Hub. Values are encrypted at rest, and the API is deliberately one-way: you can list secret *names and metadata*, set a value, and delete one — **values are never returned** by any list or read endpoint, to any scope."},"668":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-5","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#management-admin-only","content":"Secret names are env-var-safe identifiers, because that is exactly how they are delivered. The whole feature is gated on the store being enabled (an encryption key configured on the Hub); when it is not, secret-dependent runs and hooks report that configuration is required instead of failing obscurely."},"669":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-6","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"A run receives the union of:"},"670":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-7","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"the workflow's declared `workflow.secrets` list, and"},"671":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-8","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"the run input's `input.secretNames` list."},"672":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-9","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"Preflight verifies every named secret exists before the run is enqueued. At **claim time** — when a runner claims the run — the Hub decrypts exactly those named secrets into an env map that rides the claim payload, and the runner injects them **only into the workflow's child process environment**. That is the sole path a plaintext value ever leaves the store:"},"673":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-10","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"Secrets never appear in run events, logs, or the run record."},"674":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-11","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"Stored secret values are additionally scrubbed from run output and artifacts before they are persisted."},"675":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-12","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"Payload fields with credential-like names are redacted in approval cards and other presentation surfaces."},"676":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-13","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#how-runs-get-secrets","content":"Other consumers reference secrets **by name only**: hook profiles declare `secretNames`, and their readiness checks report missing *names*, never values."},"677":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-14","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"678":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-15","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"679":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-16","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"680":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-17","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/secrets`"},"681":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-18","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"`list_secrets`"},"682":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-19","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"Admin. Names and metadata only."},"683":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-20","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"`PUT /api/secrets/{key}`"},"684":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-21","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"`set_secret`"},"685":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-22","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"Admin. `{value, description?}`."},"686":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-23","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"`DELETE /api/secrets/{key}`"},"687":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-24","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"`delete_secret`"},"688":{"id":"/concepts/secrets-25","page_id":"/concepts/secrets","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/secrets#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"689":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","type":"page","content":"Tokens & Scopes","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes"},"690":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-0","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","content":"Bearer-token authentication, the scope vocabulary and presets (including read-only), the bootstrap token, and how browser and Telegram sessions work."},"691":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-1","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Scopes"},"692":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-2","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Presets"},"693":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-3","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#bootstrap-token","content":"Bootstrap token"},"694":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-4","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#browser-sessions","content":"Browser sessions"},"695":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-5","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#telegram-webapp-sessions","content":"Telegram WebApp sessions"},"696":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-6","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"697":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-7","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","content":"Every Runyard API call is authenticated with a **bearer access token**:"},"698":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-8","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","content":"`GET /api/me` (or the `whoami` MCP tool) describes the token you are holding: its name and granted scopes. Tokens are issued and revoked by admins and may carry an expiry."},"699":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-9","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"A token carries one or more scopes; each endpoint declares which scopes may call it."},"700":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-10","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Scope"},"701":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-11","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Grants"},"702":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-12","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"`api`"},"703":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-13","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Operating runs: start/preflight workflows, run drafts, reruns, promotion, cancel, resolve approvals."},"704":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-14","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"`mcp`"},"705":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-15","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"The same operating surface for MCP clients."},"706":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-16","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"`read`"},"707":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-17","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"**Read-only.** Inspect workflows, runs, logs, artifacts, approvals, schedules, runners, and the menu — and nothing else. It satisfies no mutation endpoint, so a `read`-only token can never change state."},"708":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-18","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"`runner`"},"709":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-19","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle, upload artifacts."},"710":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-20","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"`approvals`"},"711":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-21","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Resolving and creating approval cards only — the narrow scope for approval surfaces."},"712":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-22","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"`admin`"},"713":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-23","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Everything. `admin` is a **superscope**: it satisfies every scope requirement, and admin-only endpoints (tokens, secrets, catalog edits, schedules, hooks, audit) require it."},"714":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-24","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#scopes","content":"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, runners, or schedules need only an authenticated token, whatever its scopes. Runner lifecycle endpoints additionally enforce **run ownership**: only the runner token that claimed a run (or an admin) may report on it."},"715":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-25","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`GET /api/tokens/scopes` (admin; MCP tool `list_token_scopes`) describes the scope vocabulary and the named presets the Tokens page offers:"},"716":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-26","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Preset"},"717":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-27","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Scopes"},"718":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-28","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Use for"},"719":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-29","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Everything** (default)"},"720":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-30","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`api`, `mcp`, `approvals`"},"721":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-31","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"A normal person or agent: read everything, run workflows, decide approvals. No admin or runner rights."},"722":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-32","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Read-only**"},"723":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-33","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`read`"},"724":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-34","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Dashboards, monitors, and cautious integrations that must never change state."},"725":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-35","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Approvals only**"},"726":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-36","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`approvals`"},"727":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-37","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Approval inboxes and bots that only decide."},"728":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-38","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Runner**"},"729":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-39","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`runner`"},"730":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-40","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Runner machines. Keep separate from human tokens."},"731":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-41","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"**Admin**"},"732":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-42","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"`admin`"},"733":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-43","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Full control, including tokens and secrets. Issue sparingly."},"734":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-44","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#presets","content":"Finer-grained per-group write scopes (e.g. a token that can manage schedules but not run workflows) are a documented follow-up; today `api`/`mcp` grant the whole operating surface."},"735":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-45","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#bootstrap-token","content":"On first boot, if no access tokens exist, the Hub creates a `bootstrap-admin` token with the `admin`, `api`, `runner`, and `mcp` scopes and writes it to `data/bootstrap-token.txt` on the server (relative to the Hub's data directory). Use it to log in and mint narrower tokens, one per client or integration."},"736":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-46","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#browser-sessions","content":"The web app is an ordinary API client. `POST /api/auth/token-login` exchanges an access token for a **session cookie** — a signed copy of the token — so the browser session carries *exactly* the token's scopes, no extra power. Admin sections of the web app appear only for admin-scoped sessions. `POST /api/auth/logout` clears the cookie."},"737":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-47","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#telegram-webapp-sessions","content":"Approving from Telegram uses `POST /api/auth/telegram-webapp&#x60;, which verifies Telegram's signed init data against the configured bot and allowlisted users, then issues a session scoped to **`approvals` only** — narrower than any token session. A Telegram session can list and resolve approval cards but cannot start runs or touch admin surfaces."},"738":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-48","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"739":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-49","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"740":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-50","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"741":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-51","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/me`"},"742":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-52","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`whoami`"},"743":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-53","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Token name and scopes."},"744":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-54","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/tokens`"},"745":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-55","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`list_tokens`"},"746":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-56","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"747":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-57","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/tokens/scopes`"},"748":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-58","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`list_token_scopes`"},"749":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-59","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Admin. Scope vocabulary, presets, defaults."},"750":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-60","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/tokens`"},"751":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-61","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`create_token`"},"752":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-62","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Admin. `{name, scopes, expiresInDays?}`."},"753":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-63","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`DELETE /api/tokens/{id}`"},"754":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-64","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`revoke_token`"},"755":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-65","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"756":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-66","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/auth/token-login`"},"757":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-67","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"—"},"758":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-68","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Browser session bootstrap (rate-limited)."},"759":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-69","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/auth/telegram-webapp`"},"760":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-70","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"—"},"761":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-71","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Approvals-scoped Telegram session."},"762":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-72","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/auth/logout`"},"763":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-73","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"—"},"764":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-74","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Clears the session cookie."},"765":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-75","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/audit`"},"766":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-76","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"`get_audit_log`"},"767":{"id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes-77","page_id":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/tokens-and-scopes#api--mcp","content":"Admin; who did what, most recent first."},"768":{"id":"/concepts/work-items","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","type":"page","content":"Work items","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/work-items"},"769":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-0","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items","content":"Tickets on the Work board — the durable unit of company work that workflows and runs execute for."},"770":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-1","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Lifecycle"},"771":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-2","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/work-items#linked-runs-and-attention","content":"Linked runs and attention"},"772":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-3","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/work-items#execution-flow","content":"Execution flow"},"773":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-4","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"774":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-5","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items","content":"A **work item*&#x2A; (ticket) is the durable unit of company work: &#x2A;\"Make pause/resume fully supported\"&#x2A;, &#x2A;\"Fix the flaky release gate\"*. It is deliberately distinct from the two execution concepts:"},"775":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-6","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items","content":"a workflow is a reusable **recipe**;"},"776":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-7","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items","content":"a run is **one execution attempt** of a workflow."},"777":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-8","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items","content":"A work item can use one workflow, many workflows, or none yet. Many runs can attach to one work item; a run belongs to at most one work item, and old runs can stay unlinked. Crucially, **there is no failed ticket state** — run failures are execution facts, not ticket verdicts. A failed linked run parks its ticket in `blocked` with an explicit reason (see Boards → Runs move tickets); humans and agents can always re-park or retry."},"778":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-9","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Work items move through a human-legible lifecycle, shown as lanes on the Work board (`/app#work`):"},"779":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-10","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Status"},"780":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-11","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Meaning"},"781":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-12","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`intake`"},"782":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-13","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Raw ask, idea, bug, or product need."},"783":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-14","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`triaged`"},"784":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-15","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Priority, type, owner, and acceptance criteria clarified."},"785":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-16","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`ready`"},"786":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-17","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Next workflow/action selected; dependencies known."},"787":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-18","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`running`"},"788":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-19","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"One or more runs actively working on it."},"789":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-20","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`waiting`"},"790":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-21","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Paused for an approval, human decision, credential, budget, or dependency."},"791":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-22","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`blocked`"},"792":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-23","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Cannot progress without a specific intervention (`blockedReason` says which)."},"793":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-24","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`review`"},"794":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-25","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"A deliverable exists and needs inspection."},"795":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-26","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`shipped`"},"796":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-27","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Merged/released/deployed with evidence."},"797":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-28","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`accepted`"},"798":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-29","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Confirmed to satisfy the original ask."},"799":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-30","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"`archived`"},"800":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-31","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Closed historical item (hidden from lists by default)."},"801":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-32","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Status moves happen two ways, both recorded in ticket history as `work_item.status_changed` events (alongside run link/unlink events and field edits): explicit `PATCH`es by a human or agent, and automatic moves by linked runs where the mapping is reliable — a run going live puts the ticket in `running`, a held run parks it in `waiting`, a succeeded run sends it to `review`, a failed run parks it in `blocked` with a reason. Automated moves are attributed to the run (`actor: \"run:run_…\"`); see Boards for the full mapping."},"802":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-33","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#lifecycle","content":"Each item also carries `type` (`feature`, `bug`, `research`, `release`, `maintenance`, `idea`), `priority` (`urgent`, `high`, `normal`, `low`), `project`, `owner`/`requester`, `acceptanceCriteria`, `nextAction`, `blockedReason`, and an optional `dueAt`."},"803":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-34","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#linked-runs-and-attention","content":"List and detail payloads carry a linked-run rollup — `runs: { total, byStatus, lastRunAt, attention }` — where `attention` counts linked runs whose next step is a human action (`paused`, `waiting_approval`, or `budget_exceeded`), the same signal as `GET /api/runs/attention`. The board surfaces it as a badge, and linked runs also move the ticket across lanes as they progress (see Boards)."},"804":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-35","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#linked-runs-and-attention","content":"Attach runs three ways:"},"805":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-36","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#linked-runs-and-attention","content":"pass `workItemId` at run creation (`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run`, the `run_workflow` MCP tool, or `runyard run --work-item <id>`);"},"806":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-37","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#linked-runs-and-attention","content":"link an existing run: `POST /api/work-items/{id}/link-run` with `{ \"runId\": \"run_...\" }` (relinking moves the run and leaves an unlink event on the old ticket);"},"807":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-38","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#linked-runs-and-attention","content":"launch a workflow from the ticket detail in the web app."},"808":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-39","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#linked-runs-and-attention","content":"Linked runs bring their approvals and artifacts with them: the ticket detail aggregates both across all linked runs."},"809":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-40","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#execution-flow","content":"`GET /api/runs/{id}/flow` (MCP `get_run_flow`, CLI `runyard flow <runId>&#x60;) answers &#x2A;\"where is this run in its workflow?\"*. It takes the workflow's static step graph and folds the run's event stream onto it, yielding one state per step:"},"810":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-41","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#execution-flow","content":"`pending · active · done · failed · waiting · cancelled · skipped`"},"811":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-42","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#execution-flow","content":"The fold is derived, never stored: explicit `node.*` lifecycle events win; an unresolved `engine.approval.waiting` parks its step in `waiting`; the run's own terminal status closes the books (succeeded finishes unfinished active steps, cancelled cancels them, a failure-terminal status fails the step the run died on). When no source graph exists the flow degrades to an event-derived stepper rather than hiding observed work. The ticket detail renders this as the flow view for the active or latest linked run."},"812":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-43","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"813":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-44","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"814":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-45","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"815":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-46","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/work-items`"},"816":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-47","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`list_work_items`"},"817":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-48","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Filters: `status`, `project`, `owner`, `type`, `q`; `includeArchived=true` shows archived."},"818":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-49","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/work-items/{id}`"},"819":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-50","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`get_work_item`"},"820":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-51","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Item + linked runs, approvals, artifacts, ticket history."},"821":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-52","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/work-items`"},"822":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-53","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`create_work_item`"},"823":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-54","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`api`/`mcp` scope. Body: `title` (required) + the fields above."},"824":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-55","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`PATCH /api/work-items/{id}`"},"825":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-56","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`update_work_item`"},"826":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-57","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Any subset; move lanes by setting `status`."},"827":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-58","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`DELETE /api/work-items/{id}`"},"828":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-59","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`delete_work_item`"},"829":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-60","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Admin; prefer `status: \"archived\"`."},"830":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-61","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/work-items/{id}/link-run`"},"831":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-62","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`link_work_item_run`"},"832":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-63","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Body: `{ runId }`."},"833":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-64","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/work-items/{id}/unlink-run`"},"834":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-65","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`unlink_work_item_run`"},"835":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-66","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Body: `{ runId }`."},"836":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-67","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/runs/{id}/flow`"},"837":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-68","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"`get_run_flow`"},"838":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-69","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Per-step execution states for the flow view."},"839":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-70","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"CLI: `runyard work` (board list), `runyard work-item show|create|update|link|unlink`, `runyard flow <runId>`, and `runyard run <workflow> --work-item <id>`."},"840":{"id":"/concepts/work-items-71","page_id":"/concepts/work-items","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/work-items#api--mcp","content":"Grouped `/api/v1` aliases live under `/api/v1/work/items...`."},"841":{"id":"/concepts/workflows","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"page","content":"Workflows","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows"},"842":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-0","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows","content":"The catalog unit of Runyard - versioned definitions with schemas, immutable source bundles, and portable packages."},"843":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-1","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Definition"},"844":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-2","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows#workflow-source-is-data-not-files","content":"Workflow source is data, not files"},"845":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-3","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows#db-backed-workflow-bundles","content":"DB-backed workflow bundles"},"846":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-4","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows#versioning","content":"Versioning"},"847":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-5","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows#workflow-packages","content":"Workflow packages"},"848":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-6","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows#enabled-and-disabled","content":"Enabled and disabled"},"849":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-7","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"API & MCP"},"850":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-8","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows","content":"A **workflow** is the unit of the Runyard catalog: a named, versioned definition of something an agent can do. Each workflow has a slug, a display name and description, input/output schemas, and a source program that the runner executes. In older code and database tables the same object is called a *capability* — that is the legacy/internal synonym; user-facing surfaces say workflow."},"851":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-9","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"A workflow definition carries:"},"852":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-10","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Field"},"853":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-11","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Purpose"},"854":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-12","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"`slug`, `name`, `description`, `category`, `keywords`"},"855":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-13","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Identity and catalog discovery (`GET /api/workflows?q=` searches)."},"856":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-14","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"`inputSchema` / `outputSchema`"},"857":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-15","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"JSON schemas for run input and output. Required input fields drive preflight questions."},"858":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-16","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"`requiredRunnerTags`"},"859":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-17","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Tags a runner must advertise to be assigned a run."},"860":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-18","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"`requiredSkills` / `requiredAgents`"},"861":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-19","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"References into the shared catalog."},"862":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-20","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"`approvalPolicy`"},"863":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-21","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Whether new runs hold for an approval before executing."},"864":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-22","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"`workflow`"},"865":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-23","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Source configuration — most importantly `workflow.bundleId`, plus options like `hooks.allowedProfiles` for post-run hooks and `secrets` for secret delivery."},"866":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-24","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"`enabled`"},"867":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-25","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#definition","content":"Disabled workflows disappear from the catalog for non-admins and cannot be run."},"868":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-26","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#workflow-source-is-data-not-files","content":"Workflow source is created and edited through the API/MCP (`create_workflow` / `update_workflow` with inline source bytes) or by importing a workflow package. You never write workflow files to disk on the Hub or runner: custom workflows must carry source bytes or reference an existing `workflow.bundleId` — bare `workflow.entry` file paths are rejected."},"869":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-27","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#db-backed-workflow-bundles","content":"Published source lives in the Hub database as **workflow bundles**: immutable, hash-addressed rows in the `workflow_bundles` table. Publishing is insert-only — every publish creates a new `(workflow slug, version)` row with a `sha256` of the source, so a bundle id permanently names the exact bytes that were published. Bundles are capped at 500 KB, listing never returns source bytes, and a workflow that references a missing bundle fails preflight rather than silently falling back to a file."},"870":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-28","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#db-backed-workflow-bundles","content":"Prefer `create_workflow` / `update_workflow` with inline source — they publish a bundle for you and point the workflow at it."},"871":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-29","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#versioning","content":"Updating a workflow bumps its integer `version` and snapshots the previous definition. `GET /api/workflows/{name}/versions` lists the versions observed on past runs, and every run records the `workflowVersion` it executed. Bundle versions count separately, per publish."},"872":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-30","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#workflow-packages","content":"A **workflow package** is a portable `.runyard-workflow.json` file for moving a workflow between Hubs. Exports contain source bytes, metadata, requirements, and content/workflow hashes — never secret values. Imports publish the source as a new immutable bundle and create the workflow **disabled by default**, so an admin can configure and preflight it locally before enabling it. `validate` and `preview` let you check a package without writing anything."},"873":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-31","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#enabled-and-disabled","content":"`DELETE /api/workflows/{id}` disables a workflow rather than erasing it: historical runs stay intact, non-admins get a 404, and preflight blocks new runs until an admin re-enables it with `PATCH /api/workflows/{id}`."},"874":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-32","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Endpoint"},"875":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-33","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"MCP tool"},"876":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-34","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Notes"},"877":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-35","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/workflows`"},"878":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-36","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`list_workflows`, `search_workflows`"},"879":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-37","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`?q=` searches."},"880":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-38","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/workflows`"},"881":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-39","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`create_workflow`"},"882":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-40","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin. Inline source or `workflow.bundleId`."},"883":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-41","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/workflows/{id}`"},"884":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-42","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`describe_workflow`"},"885":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-43","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Definition and input schema."},"886":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-44","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`PATCH /api/workflows/{id}`"},"887":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-45","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`update_workflow`"},"888":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-46","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"889":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-47","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`DELETE /api/workflows/{id}`"},"890":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-48","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`delete_workflow`"},"891":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-49","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin; disables."},"892":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-50","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/workflows/{id}/source`"},"893":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-51","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`get_workflow_source`"},"894":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-52","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Source, metadata, sections, graph."},"895":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-53","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/workflows/{name}/versions`"},"896":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-54","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`list_workflow_versions`"},"897":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-55","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Versions seen on runs."},"898":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-56","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/workflow-bundles`"},"899":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-57","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`list_workflow_bundles`"},"900":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-58","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Metadata only."},"901":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-59","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/workflow-bundles/{id}`"},"902":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-60","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`get_workflow_bundle`"},"903":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-61","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Includes source."},"904":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-62","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/workflow-bundles`"},"905":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-63","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`publish_workflow_bundle`"},"906":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-64","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"907":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-65","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`GET /api/workflow-packages/workflows/{id}/export`"},"908":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-66","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`export_workflow_package`"},"909":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-67","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"910":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-68","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/workflow-packages/validate`"},"911":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-69","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`validate_workflow_package`"},"912":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-70","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin."},"913":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-71","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/workflow-packages/preview`"},"914":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-72","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`preview_workflow_import`"},"915":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-73","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin; nothing written."},"916":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-74","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`POST /api/workflow-packages/import`"},"917":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-75","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"`import_workflow_package`"},"918":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-76","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Admin; imports disabled."},"919":{"id":"/concepts/workflows-77","page_id":"/concepts/workflows","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/workflows#api--mcp","content":"Running a workflow (`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run`, `run_workflow`) and preflighting it are covered on the Runs page."},"920":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"page","content":"Building agents on Runyard","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers"},"921":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-0","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers","content":"Discovery surfaces, the API-first guarantee, and recommended etiquette for agents and third-party clients."},"922":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-1","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Discovery surfaces"},"923":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-2","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#the-api-first-guarantee","content":"The API-first guarantee"},"924":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-3","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#auth-expectations","content":"Auth expectations"},"925":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-4","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"Recommended agent etiquette"},"926":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-5","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#push-instead-of-poll-response-endpoints","content":"Push instead of poll: response endpoints"},"927":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-6","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#machine-intake-workflow-endpoints","content":"Machine intake: workflow endpoints"},"928":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-7","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers","content":"Runyard treats agents as first-class API consumers. This page covers how a client discovers what a Hub can do, what it may rely on, and how to be a good citizen."},"929":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-8","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Surface"},"930":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-9","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Auth"},"931":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-10","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"What it gives you"},"932":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-11","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /llms.txt`"},"933":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-12","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"none"},"934":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-13","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Static, generic orientation for agents: what Runyard is, its tool names, the run path. It deliberately contains nothing deployment-specific and points at the authenticated menu."},"935":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-14","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /openapi.json`"},"936":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-15","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"none"},"937":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-16","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The full HTTP surface, generated from the Hub's API surface registry — it cannot drift from the routes the server actually registers."},"938":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-17","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"MCP `tools/list`"},"939":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-18","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"token"},"940":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-19","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The complete MCP tool set (parity-tested against the API surface). Connect with `runyard mcp install` or the `runyard-mcp` stdio server."},"941":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-20","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /api/menu` / `get_menu`"},"942":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-21","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"token"},"943":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-22","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The live, private catalog: workflows with schemas, execution modes, runner pool state, and ready-to-use CLI/MCP invocations."},"944":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-23","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Start every session with `get_menu` (or `GET /api/menu`), then `describe_workflow` for anything you intend to run."},"945":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-24","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#the-api-first-guarantee","content":"The web app is an ordinary client of the same HTTP API, with no privileged endpoints. Every route is declared in one registry that also generates `openapi.json` and is parity-tested against the MCP tool list — so a lossless third-party client is possible by construction: anything the web app can show or do, your client can too, over HTTP or MCP."},"946":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-25","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#auth-expectations","content":"Ask the Hub's administrator for a scoped access token (admins issue them from the Connect tab or `POST /api/tokens`). Agents typically need `api` and/or `mcp` — nothing more. Send it as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every HTTP call, or configure it for the MCP server. Never ask for or expect the bootstrap/admin token."},"947":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-26","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Set `input.title`.** For agent-created runs, include a short human-readable title (\"Audit checkout flow mobile states\") so run lists, approval cards, and human handoff stay decipherable."},"948":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-27","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Preflight first.** When input is rough or unverified, call `preflight_workflow` (`POST /api/workflows/{id}/preflight`) or pass `negotiate: true` to `run_workflow`. You get `ready | needs_input | blocked` with concrete questions and blockers instead of a run that fails."},"949":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-28","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Use run drafts for question/answer loops.** `create_run_draft` creates a proposed run and preflights it; `update_run_draft` merges answers into the input and re-preflights; `submit_run_draft` enqueues the real run only once it is ready; `discard_run_draft` abandons it. Nothing executes until submit."},"950":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-29","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Poll the timeline with `since` cursors.** `get_run_timeline` (`GET /api/runs/{id}/timeline`) returns a unified, ascending view of status transitions, events, and artifacts. Pass the previous response's `nextSince` as `since` so the Hub never re-sends what you have. Fetch results with `get_run_status`, `get_run_logs`, and `get_run_artifacts` / `download_artifact`."},"951":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-30","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Cap what a run may spend.** Pass `budget: { maxTokens, maxCostMicros }` when starting a run; a breach hard-stops the run as the distinct terminal status `budget_exceeded` (never a silent overrun). Read spend as you go from the run's `usage` and `budgetStatus` fields, and use `get_usage_summary` for a fleet rollup. See Usage metering & budgets."},"952":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-31","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Expect paused runs, and resume them.** A run interrupted by exhausted provider credits/quota parks as `paused` instead of failing. Check `run.pause` for the reason and required action, fix it, then `resume_run` (`POST /api/runs/{id}/resume`) — it continues from the engine checkpoint when one exists."},"953":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-32","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Triage with the attention queue.** `list_attention_runs` (`GET /api/runs/attention`) returns everything waiting on a human — paused, awaiting approval, or recently budget-stopped — with counts. Poll it instead of scanning full run lists for stuck work."},"954":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-33","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"A metered, resumable run end to end:"},"955":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-34","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#push-instead-of-poll-response-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run` accepts an optional `responseEndpoint` (`{ \"type\": \"http\" | \"telegram\", \"config\": { ... } }`). When the run reaches a terminal state, the Hub POSTs a sanitized payload to your HTTP endpoint (or sends a concise Telegram message). Delivery state is visible on `GET /api/runs/{id}` under `responseEndpoints[]`, and polling remains the canonical fallback."},"956":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-35","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#machine-intake-workflow-endpoints","content":"For fixed-purpose integrations that should not hold a Hub token at all (webhooks, form intake, external systems), an admin can configure a **workflow endpoint**: `POST /api/workflow-endpoints/{slug}` accepts a payload authenticated with that endpoint's own secret, rate-limited, size-capped, and deduplicated, and triggers exactly one preconfigured workflow. This is the narrowest possible credential to hand to an external system."},"957":{"id":"/guides/api","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"page","content":"HTTP API","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/api"},"958":{"id":"/guides/api-0","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api","content":"Authenticate, discover, and drive workflow runs over the Runyard Hub's HTTP API."},"959":{"id":"/guides/api-1","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Authentication"},"960":{"id":"/guides/api-2","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"Discovery"},"961":{"id":"/guides/api-3","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"API groups and `/api/v1` aliases"},"962":{"id":"/guides/api-4","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"The typical flow"},"963":{"id":"/guides/api-5","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Key endpoints"},"964":{"id":"/guides/api-6","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"Approvals"},"965":{"id":"/guides/api-7","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#run-drafts","content":"Run drafts"},"966":{"id":"/guides/api-8","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#error-conventions","content":"Error conventions"},"967":{"id":"/guides/api-9","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#rate-limits","content":"Rate limits"},"968":{"id":"/guides/api-10","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#see-also","content":"See also"},"969":{"id":"/guides/api-11","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api","content":"Every Runyard surface — the web app, the CLI, and the MCP server — is an\nordinary client of one HTTP API served by the Hub. Anything they can do, you\ncan do with `curl`."},"970":{"id":"/guides/api-12","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Send an access token as a bearer token on every request:"},"971":{"id":"/guides/api-13","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Tokens are minted by an admin (web UI, `POST /api/tokens`, or the CLI) and carry\n**scopes**:"},"972":{"id":"/guides/api-14","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Scope"},"973":{"id":"/guides/api-15","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Grants"},"974":{"id":"/guides/api-16","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`api`"},"975":{"id":"/guides/api-17","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Start runs, preflight, drafts, rerun/cancel/promote, create approvals"},"976":{"id":"/guides/api-18","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`mcp`"},"977":{"id":"/guides/api-19","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"The same operations, issued for MCP clients"},"978":{"id":"/guides/api-20","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`read`"},"979":{"id":"/guides/api-21","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"**Read-only** — inspect workflows, runs, logs, artifacts, approvals, schedules, and runners; satisfies no mutation endpoint"},"980":{"id":"/guides/api-22","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`runner`"},"981":{"id":"/guides/api-23","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle events and artifacts"},"982":{"id":"/guides/api-24","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`approvals`"},"983":{"id":"/guides/api-25","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Resolve approval cards (approve / reject / request changes) and create them"},"984":{"id":"/guides/api-26","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`admin`"},"985":{"id":"/guides/api-27","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"**Superscope** — satisfies every scope requirement, plus admin-only surfaces: tokens, secrets, audit log, schedules, workflow create/update, packages, hooks, updates"},"986":{"id":"/guides/api-28","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`GET /api/tokens/scopes` (admin) returns this vocabulary plus named presets —\n**everything** (`api`+`mcp`+`approvals`, the default), **read-only**,\n**approvals-only**, **runner**, and **admin** — which the Tokens page uses."},"987":{"id":"/guides/api-29","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, or artifacts require any authenticated\ntoken. A token with only the `read` scope is therefore read-only: it can\ninspect everything non-admin but every create/update/delete/run/approve call\nfails with `403`. A request with no valid token gets\n`401 {\"error\": \"unauthorized\"}`; a token missing a required scope gets:"},"988":{"id":"/guides/api-30","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"with status `403`. `GET /api/me` describes the calling token (name and scopes)."},"989":{"id":"/guides/api-31","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /openapi.json`** (unauthenticated) — generated from the server's API\nsurface registry, the single source of truth every route is registered from,\nso **every endpoint is documented there**. This guide covers the important\nones; use `/openapi.json` for the full list."},"990":{"id":"/guides/api-32","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /api/menu`** (authenticated) — the agent-facing menu: workflow catalog,\nlocal/remote execution modes, and follow-up paths. The same data backs the\nMCP `get_menu` tool and `/llms.txt`."},"991":{"id":"/guides/api-33","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /api/version`** (unauthenticated) — product name, version, instance\nname."},"992":{"id":"/guides/api-34","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Operations are organized into eight groups, exposed as OpenAPI tags:\n**workflows**, **runs**, **approvals**, **automation** (schedules + workflow\nendpoints), **library** (agents, skills, knowledge, hooks), **distribution**\n(bundles, packages), **admin** (tokens, secrets, audit, alerts, updates), and\n**system** (health, version, menu, dashboard, runners)."},"993":{"id":"/guides/api-35","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Every grouped operation is also reachable at a stable `/api/v1` alias that\nmakes the group visible in the path — for example:"},"994":{"id":"/guides/api-36","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Canonical"},"995":{"id":"/guides/api-37","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Grouped alias"},"996":{"id":"/guides/api-38","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/workflows`"},"997":{"id":"/guides/api-39","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/workflows`"},"998":{"id":"/guides/api-40","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id`"},"999":{"id":"/guides/api-41","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/runs/:id`"},"1000":{"id":"/guides/api-42","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/run-drafts`"},"1001":{"id":"/guides/api-43","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/runs/drafts`"},"1002":{"id":"/guides/api-44","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/schedules`"},"1003":{"id":"/guides/api-45","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/automation/schedules`"},"1004":{"id":"/guides/api-46","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/agents`"},"1005":{"id":"/guides/api-47","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/library/agents`"},"1006":{"id":"/guides/api-48","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/workflow-bundles`"},"1007":{"id":"/guides/api-49","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/distribution/bundles`"},"1008":{"id":"/guides/api-50","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/tokens`"},"1009":{"id":"/guides/api-51","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/admin/tokens`"},"1010":{"id":"/guides/api-52","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/menu`"},"1011":{"id":"/guides/api-53","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/system/menu`"},"1012":{"id":"/guides/api-54","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Aliases are the same registry entries registered twice, so they always share\nthe canonical route's handler, auth, and scopes; in `openapi.json` each alias\ncarries `x-canonical-path`. Unversioned `/api/...` paths remain fully\nsupported — use whichever reads better. The legacy `/api/capabilities/*`\npaths are deprecated aliases of `/api/workflows/*` and get no `/api/v1` form;\nnew clients should say *workflow* everywhere."},"1013":{"id":"/guides/api-55","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"List workflows, preflight your input, start the run, then poll it:"},"1014":{"id":"/guides/api-56","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"For agent-created runs, include a short human-readable `input.title` — it labels\nrun lists, approval cards, and handoffs. `executionMode` is `local` or `remote`;\n`run` also accepts an optional `responseEndpoint` (`{type: http|telegram,\nconfig}`) to have the terminal-state reply delivered when the run finishes\n(polling `/api/runs/:id` remains the canonical fallback), and an optional\n`budget` (`{maxTokens?, maxCostMicros?}`, also accepted as `input.budget`) that\nhard-caps the run's metered model usage — a breach terminates the run with the\ndistinct status `budget_exceeded`. Metered usage aggregates onto every run\nobject as `usage` and is detailed at `GET /api/runs/:id/usage`; see\nUsage metering & budgets."},"1015":{"id":"/guides/api-57","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"With `\"negotiate\": true`, a non-ready request returns the negotiation state\n(questions, blockers, warnings, plus a saved draft) instead of creating a run —\nfix the input and call again."}