se the bootstrap token until you mint one."],[462,"The runner observes the terminal status on its next poll and cancels the detached engine run, and the gateway refuses further calls from that run's token (`403`)."],[522,"The runner protocol endpoints intentionally have no MCP tools — they are Hub↔runner machinery, not an operator surface."],[981,"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle events and artifacts"],[709,"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle, upload artifacts."],[1526,"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle."],[1566,"The runner's preflight refused to execute (missing workflow source, auth not ready, repo path problems)."],[626,"The RunYard Development Factory example also ships a disabled daily `product-workflow` schedule for roadmap shaping: `0 9 * * *` in `America/New_York`, `execute: true`, and `laneId: \"triaged\"`. When an operator enables it, the child implementation runs execute sequentially in isolated review branches; `main` is changed only by explicit promotion."],[36,"The same data lives at `GET /api/runs/{id}`, `/api/runs/{id}/timeline`, `/api/runs/{id}/logs`, and `/api/runs/{id}/artifacts`, and in the web run page — the Hub is the source of truth even when execution happened on a local runner."],[705,"The same operating surface for MCP clients."],[1524,"The same operations over the MCP server."],[977,"The same operations, issued for MCP clients"],[23,"The script never prints secrets, never applies updates automatically, and prints a Caddy reverse-proxy snippet if you want TLS in front (recommended for anything non-local — see the security guide)."],[171,"The seeded RunYard Factory board uses conservative triggers:"],[1401,"The server exposes tools generated from the same API surface registry\nthe Hub's routes and `/openapi.json` come from. Grouped by resource:"],[1396,"The server name is `runyard` for the default remote and `runyard-<remote>` for\n