 use it:"],[185,"Ticket moves to"],[202,"Tickets in `shipped`, `accepted`, or `archived` are never touched, and terminal outcomes (`succeeded`/`failed`) wait until no sibling linked run is still live. Every automated move lands in ticket history as a `work_item.status_changed` event attributed to the run (`actor: \"run:run_…\"`), with the reason."],[769,"Tickets on the Work board — the durable unit of company work that workflows and runs execute for."],[1120,"Timed approvals and fallback"],[92,"Timed approvals with fallback"],[1395,"To configure a client by hand, print the snippet instead:"],[30,"To run an ad-hoc runner on any other machine (for example your laptop, for `local` execution):"],[939,"token"],[942,"token"],[743,"Token name and scopes."],[1422,"Tokens"],[689,"Tokens & Scopes"],[971,"Tokens are minted by an admin (web UI, `POST /api/tokens`, or the CLI) and carry\n**scopes**:"],[1518,"Tokens carry scopes; admins mint them from the Connect tab or `POST /api/tokens`."],[1248,"Tokens, audit, and catalog"],[1403,"Tools"],[1444,"Tools marked † require an admin-scoped token."],[155,"Transition policy"],[1238,"Translate each workflow's `on:` triggers and jobs into the schema above; move repository secrets into the hub's secrets and reference them **by name** in `secrets:`; replace `runs-on` with runner tags + trust policy; keep the GitHub merge-gate by marking the `runyard/*` checks required in branch protection. Explicitly out of scope for now (planned follow-ups, not silently emulated): `act`-style local Actions compatibility, merge queues / speculative gating (Zuul-style), Kubernetes/Tekton executors, and release automation."],[1462,"Trigger"],[381,"Trigger a preview deploy for a configured project."],[1196,"Troubleshooting"],[1543,"Troubleshooting"],[1493,"Trust boundary"],[1492,"Trust boundary, token scopes, secrets handling, runner sandboxing, and production posture for a Runyard deployment."],[266,"Trust model and fork security"],[1211,"Trust policy governs secrets and native execution (see the trust model). `--runner-tags build,fast` additionally restricts this repository's jobs to runners carrying those tags."],[1283,"Turn a machine into a runner in three steps. First scaffold a workspace\n(requires `bun` and the `smithers` engine on `PATH`; it warns if no `claude`,\n`codex`, or `pi` agent CLI is found):"],[1517,"Two narrow exceptions authenticate by other means: `POST /api/telegram/webhook` is verified against the configured bot and webhook secret, and `POST /api/workflow-endpoints/{slug}` submissions authenticate with that endpoint's own secret (below). `GET /api/setup` returns only a reduced identity payload (instance name, auth mode) to unauthenticated callers."],[1584,"Unclassified failure."],[1036,"Unified ascending timeline (`since=<iso>`, `limit=<n>`); backs `runyard tail`"],[1602,"Unified timeline: status transitions, events, artifacts as NDJSON."],[1251,"Updating a host install"],[1611,"Updating a workflow"],[871,"Updating a workflow bumps its integer `version` and snapshots the previous definition. `GET /api/workflows/{name}/versions` lists the versions observed on past runs, and every run records the `workflowVersion` it executed. Bundle versions count separately, per publish."],[528,"Usage and budgets"],[467,"Usage is captured at the **inference boundary**, through two paths:"],[436,"Usage metering & budgets"],[438,"Usage records and the run aggregate"],[1445,"Use `run_schedule_now` when an external cron or agent should appear as\nScheduled automation in RunYard. Direct `run_workflow` calls keep their\nMCP/token provenance and are not relabeled as scheduled runs."],[718,"Use for"],[1213,"Validation errors are shown by `GET /api/ci/repos/:id/config`, the repository page in the web app, and — for triggered pipelines — as a failed `runyard/ci` check on the commit."],[114,"Values"],[1170,"Variable"],[1341,"Variable"],[1362,"Variable"],[22,"Verify the Hub is up:"],[1595,"Verify, in order: `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` and `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_CHAT_ID` are set on the Hub; the bot's webhook points at `https://hub.example.com/api/telegram/webhook` with the matching `TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET`; the bot is a member of the target chat; and the users pressing buttons are listed in `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_USER_IDS`. Response-endpoint deliveries record their state (`status`, `attempts`, `last_error`) on `GET /api/runs/{id}` under `responseEndpoints[]`."],[846,"Versioning"],[1453,"Versioning and releases"],[897,"Versions seen on runs."],[324,"View"],[340,"Visual graph tab."],[1570,"Wait and re-run; check the provider account."],[1244,"Watch and manage runs"],[1129,"Web app"],[33,"Web: open **Workflows**, pick &#x2A;*Hello (Smithers proof)**, fill in `topic`, and click Run."],[1123,"Webhook"],[1222,"Webhook answers `401 invalid signature`"],[1224,"Webhook answers `503`"],[278,"Webhook delivery + redelivery"],[617,"What a fire produces"],[1141,"What each decision does depends on the card's kind:"],[1,"What is Runyard"],[1463,"What it does"],[931,"What it gives you"],[48,"What it is"],[206,"What it matches"],[97,"What it represents"],[1598,"What it tells you"],[1500,"What stays out of public discovery docs"],[1624,"What the workflow does; shown in the catalog and menus."],[1561,"What to do"],[363,"When an agent hands off to a human — \"approve this\", \"read the logs\" — prefer relaying the payload's deep link over describing where to click."],[180,"When enabled, the daily run queues compact implementation runs sequentially. Each child pushes an isolated review branch targeting `main`; operators inspect and promote the successful branch before `main` changes."],[555,"When execution is interrupted by a condition a human can fix — the classic case is **the provider account ran out of credits** — the run parks as `paused` instead of failing. Pause metadata lives on `run.pause`:"],[1317,"When it finishes it prints next steps: sign in with the bootstrap token, mint a\nrunner-scoped token, put it in `/e